with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #2820&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 6bba4042b09110c8da016897b2f744e411bfb6bb&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Till Rohrmann &amp;lt;trohrmann@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2016-11-16T17:33:54Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5082&quot; title=&quot;Pull ExecutionService lifecycle management out of the JobManager&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-5082&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-5082&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Pull ExecutorService lifecycle management out of the JobManager&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The provided ExecutorService will no longer be closed by the JobManager. Instead the&lt;br/&gt;
    lifecycle is managed outside of it where it was created. This will give a nicer behaviour,&lt;br/&gt;
    because it better seperates responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;

